“When Sam told me to check out his new DEATHWESTERN amp plug-in from @purafiedaudio my immediate response was “Why would I ever listen to advice from a hippy stoner loser that I could destroy with one punch about tone?” I mean seriously. This clown shows me stupid Jim Lill YouTube videos about guitar tones like it’s some divine revelation. But because we’re friends I decided to give it a shot. I honestly couldn’t believe how incredible it sounded. More importantly it felt really authentic. I immediately FaceTimed Sam and had him show me the exact signal flow he used. A few of the ingredients I was missing so I purchased an Orange Cab and an @evertune guitar to try it for myself. I couldn’t believe the results. I immediately ordered several DEATHWESTERN amps from him each with a different preamp and power amp stage. That way I could have all the possible options covered here at my new studio. Who would have known that pop punk loser knew something about metal guitar tone?!” - Mark Lewis. (The world’s best audio engineer of all time)

This is your sonic jackhammer for concrete wall mixes. Try it on anything you want to add pumpy, aggressive life to and find yourself addicted.

Introducing the newest plug-in from @purafiedaudio: the SLP 538 EQ 🐼💜🎛️

Rehab for EQ Tweakers

The SLP 538 EQ from @purafiedaudio is your new channel EQ if you like to actually finish mixes. We started with producer Sam Pura’s favorite, criminally underappreciated, streamlined variant of the best sounding console EQ. Then we genetically spliced it with the sought-after stepped-knob workflow of its direct competitor, delivering the best of all hardware tone shapers in one impossible plugin. To make this the last EQ you’ll ever need, it also has auto gain to stop volume creep, built-in filters, phase inversion, and our obligatory THD knob. It sounds good on practically everything. Our mission is to make every EQ move effective and obvious by cutting out variables, giving you a sound you love as fast as possible. Forget staring at squiggly yellow lines for hours; it’s time to stop letting your eyes dictate your sound. 🐼💜🎛️

I’ve spent my entire career unhappy with the ITB EQ options, and always preferred to use my analog hardware units instead. This SLP 538 EQ is the first and only EQ I feel confident using ITB on every single channel of audio every day. I love it and I know you will too. Give it a try @purafiedaudio 🐼💜🎛️

What are you liking the @purafiedaudio SLP 538 EQ on?! I love it on Drum Channels, Bass, and Guitar. My favorite thing to do is to carve away mids with the auto gain on. It’s super easy to hear where the frequency range opens up without hearing the channel volume decrease. Also I love setting the Hi freq band all the way to the top and cranking it. It’s a fun trick to use on Overheads and anything you want to sound bright without sounding harsh. 🐼💜🎛️

I saw this on @lxestrada’s story and felt inclined to post and share it. It’s insanely true. I’m constantly shocked how little information is available on a song’s producer credit tag on a Spotify song. Big artists, small artists, everyone blows it on crediting the production team. Some of my “biggest” albums don’t even credit me. Then I’ll have clients who are serious best friends that go above and beyond to credit me and still somehow leave this one blank on their Spotify. I’ve even had people tell me about albums I’ve produced and attempted to correct me when I tell them I produced it because they didn’t see and or read otherwise. This seemingly small and or little thing honestly can greatly impact audio peoples lives. From educating curious audio fans to educating curious artists that might consider reaching out for future work... Producers, songwriters, anyone involved in making music really need to be credited properly and everyone involved in posting music to Spotify and even a YouTube music video needs to make a more conscious effort to support and credit all the audio people involved in making the final product.

Back in 2005, @adrianrobison unexpectedly reached out to me, offering a life-changing opportunity: to join his band @wearestrata on tour as a guitar tech. He was the one who showed me the ropes and set me on my path, teaching me not just the basics of drum maintenance, like changing heads and tuning, but also more advanced techniques like recording, editing, and placing drum samples with precision. Adrian was a talented punisher who had built up an impressive collection of drum samples by simply asking every legendary engineer he worked with if they had any to share. To this day, I still use dozens of those samples.

Although it has been over a decade since I last saw Adrian, it was wonderful to catch up and reminisce about the wild experiences and stories we shared during Strata's last album cycle. We've been through some incredible highs and lows together, but every moment was worth it. Adrian wasn't just a colleague - he was a true best friend. Thanks for the great hangout and catch-up, dude!

Introducing the newest plug-in from @purafiedaudio: The Panda Rooms!

Natural Studio Wetness

Get lifetime virtual access to the 10 versatile room vibes artisanally crafted in producer Sam Pura’s Panda Studios, each captured with 5 tried and true microphone combinations. You deserve to tune your room glue and effect reverbs like you booked infinite studio time, minus Sam’s meticulous and demanding (read: nerdy) recording process. As you mix in and out room mics, the Panda Rooms will optionally autocorrect the gain, so you can isolate the character of each microphone type and placement. Rather than fiddle with “diffusion” and “space” knobs looking for something more fitting, skip the effort and start straight away with the studio sound that’s already been proven on dozens of records before. Besides, everyone knows that natural wetness always beats artificial.

I was real stoked and proud to watch this @chrisgarza interview with @spiritworldprophet on the @garzapodcastofficial. Whenever artists ask me about records I’m proud of, or what I’m currently working on that I’m stoked on, I always go right to “Spiritworld” and if you watch this whole video you’ll understand why. 

It’s incredibly rare to be able to work with someone that understands and respects the craft of audio production and fully recognizes that “The Studio” is the best musical instrument of all time. No ego vanity bullshit. Spiritworld is focused specifically on the content and the quality of the end result. The only thing that matters is the music.

It’s truly a blessing to be able to make music and records with them. I highly reccomend you check this out. You’ll walk away more inspired. 🐼💜

Sam Pura has had enough of listening to other people’s depressing tracking sessions. He would try to fix it with in-the-box compressors, but just left the experience feeling like something, some time long ago, had gone horribly wrong. To resolve this, Purafied put together a custom VCA compressor signal chain meant to go on every channel, and modeled it into a plugin that is as easy to use as a single piece of gear. This way, if sound ever came to Sam without having passed through the compression stack first (gross), he could correct it after the fact by using the same exact sound of his hardware as a single plugin instance. As a side effect of this, you too now have this capability, so we expect your music to be more modern and tight in the future. We’re always listening.

The LED Compressor is available now for an introductory price of $38

We can’t remember what life was like before this compressor, and we don’t want to. The modern, glossy, sound that cleans up unfocused or otherwise embarrassing tracks has now been transmogrified into a plugin, infused with the Purafied workflow that gets your mixes out the door. A holy marriage of auto gain, three variable saturation modes, and straightforward controls make this a no-brainer insert to tighten up any track or bus. Despite how it may appear, this is a custom multi-step signal chain built around producer Sam Pura’s favorite VCA compressors, including their iconic LED gain reduction meters which lend the plugin its name. It’s anything but a simple model emulation you can find elsewhere. Forged over a decade into an “always in” channel and bus compressor, this performance enhancing plugin is impossible to quit.

The LED Compressor is available now for an introductory price of $38
